Exception java
   exception is an unwanted behavior from the application that disrupt  the normal flow-
   application.

exception handling is covering the complex system error massage to user friendly  error massage.

friendly error massage
   which are understand by common people we provide back up code that use used if our primary logic fails.

Why we should handle exception
   1)to make the software user friendly
   2)it helps use make more robust (better) application
   3)we can figure out the exact line numbers and issue that are causing program in our code
   (most in for all type of program).
   what is the syntax how do i use exception handling in my code
   we have new keywords like try catch,  finally  throw,  and throws.
Ex:
  try {
  we put that part of the code here that ca cause exceptions.or problematic code.
  }catch(create a variables  of the class whose exception can throw){
  back up code here
  }
  throw and throws exception..
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Exceptions happen when there is an error in the code or a file is not found. There are 2 type of exceptions
  1- Checked exceptions
  2- Unchecked exceptions
  How we handle exceptions?
  With try and catch blocks, we put the code which we think will give us error in
  the try block and the type of exceptions we expect we put in the catch block.
